description.narrative: Output 1.5: The Malaysian private sector has increased knowledge and commitment to its responsibility to respect children's rights, and can access quality technical support and capacity for implementing the CRBP., which contributes to Private Sector Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: By 2020, all children in Malaysia benefit from strengthened national policies, quality social services and capacities that enhance well-being and enable them to survive, thrive and develop to their full potential.

description.narrative: Selected private sector partners continue to adopt UNICEF's Children's Rights and Business Principles to champion children's rights in business whilst working towards achieving goals outlined in Agenda 2030 and Malaysia's Shared Prosperity Vision. Private sector is playing a critical role by working with industry regulators to strengthen online child protection, sharing of best business practices amongst peers, supporting nationwide campaigns, and pioneering an inclusive and human-centered designed playground. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
